Package: MicroTrace
Title: Lightweight SNP-based Clustering Tool for Outbreak Detection
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
  person("Kaitao", "Lai", email = "drktla@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
)
Description: MicroTrace identifies clusters of pathogen genomes based on pairwise SNP distances for real-time outbreak tracking. Designed in R, it supports metadata integration, dendrogram visualization, SNP histogram/density plotting, intra-cluster SNP summary statistics, and automatic threshold suggestions. It generates a reproducible HTML report for public health communication and outbreak monitoring.
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports:
    ape,
    readr,
    ggplot2,
    dendextend,
    dplyr
Suggests:
    testthat,
    rmarkdown
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
URL: https://github.com/biosciences/MicroTrace
BugReports: https://github.com/biosciences/MicroTrace/issues
